1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:20,602
Lighting is chosen from drawings and catalogs, but homeowners cannot easily
imagine the atmosphere it will create.

2
00:00:20,602 --> 00:00:25,132
Fixing a poor choice after construction can cost real money.

3
00:00:25,132 --> 00:00:40,632
Lighting Lab lets homeowners try lighting plans in their own floor plan,
with no CAD skills required. Import your own floor plan in the browser.

4
00:00:40,632 --> 00:00:53,661
Select a light and change its color temperature
from warm 2700K to 3500K.

5
00:00:53,661 --> 00:01:04,941
Lower or raise brightness, compare another position,
and adjust how widely the light spreads.

6
00:01:04,941 --> 00:01:19,044
Try several options in 2D, then switch to 3D
to see the walls, furniture, and room as a whole.

7
00:01:19,044 --> 00:01:34,058
The finished look includes indirect light.
Compare options until they fit how you want to use the room.

8
00:01:34,058 --> 00:01:45,073
2D and 3D stay in sync, and projects save and reopen
in the browser—on a PC or a phone.

9
00:01:45,073 --> 00:02:12,264
Codex with GPT-5.6 reviewed believable lighting and everyday-device performance,
then supported mobile improvements, English, tests, and the public release.

10
00:02:12,264 --> 00:02:22,617
Compare color temperature, brightness, position, and distribution
in your own floor plan—before construction.
